\begin_layout Standard

\series medium
Spread vs.
 Skill plots are widely used to evaluate the quality of ensemble forecasting
 systems.
 One goal of ensemble forecasting is to have the ensemble members represent
 the range of possible outcomes, which suggests that the ensemble spread
 shoud approsimately equal the skill of the ensemble mean (as measured by
 RMSE).
 Spread and skill will be plotted on the y-axis, and the user may select
 the x axis variable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Details
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:SpreadSkill-Plot-Details"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series medium
Selection of options to produce your plot proceeds approxately counter-clockwise
 around the METViewer window.
 Select your database from the pulldown menus at the top margin of the METViewer
 window.
 Make sure the 'Series' tab is selected near the top left, just under the
 database pulldown menu.
 Next, you must select the type of MET statistics that will be used to create
 the plot.
 In the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Plot Data
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 menu, the list contains 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Stat
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

MODE
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

MODE-TD
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 For details about these types of output statistics in MET, please see the
 most recent version of the MET Users' Guide (
\begin_inset Flex URL
status open

